    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Temperature &gt; 38 degrees Celcius

          -  New infiltrate on chest x-ray

          -  Increased C-reactive protein (CRP)

          -  Either cough, dyspnea, pleuritic chest pain, expectoration, or tachypnea

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  patients referred from the intensive care unit

          -  reduced cognitive awareness if not able to able to cooperate with the assessment of
             oropharyngeal dysphagia
      </textblock>
